## 3. Marketing Strategy: "Rewrite the Narrative"

### Go-to-Market Strategy: "Visual Storytelling"
*   **Campaign**: **"Title: Untitled"**
    *   Launch teaser showing models ripping labels off clothes and stamping "RETITLED" over them.
*   **Content Pillars**:
    1.  **Behind the Seams**: Raw, unedited footage of the design process. Highlighting the "Ultra High Quality".
    2.  **The Fluid Test**: Side-by-side videos of the same item on a 5'2" femme model and a 6'1" mascot/male model. Caption: "Fits everyone. Titles irrelevant."

### "Fluid Fashion" Angle
*   Market the clothing not as "Unisex" (which sounds boring/shapeless) but as **"Universal Structure"**.
*   Use "Architecture" terminology instead of fashion terms (e.g., "Structural fit" vs "Baggy").

---

## 4. Technical Architecture

### The Stack (Modern & High-Performance)
*   **Framework**: [Next.js 14 (App Router)](https://nextjs.org/) - For SEO and React Server Components.
*   **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) - For rapid, custom design implementation.
*   **Animations**: [Framer Motion](https://www.framer.com/motion/) - Critical for the "liquid" transitions.
*   **Backend/DB**: [Supabase](https://supabase.com/) - PostgreSQL database for inventory and auth.
*   **Image/Video**: [Cloudinary](https://cloudinary.com/) or Vercel Blob - For optimizing the heavy video content.
*   **State**: [Zustand](https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand) - Distinct from Redux, simpler for UI state.

### Phase 1: MVP (Landing Page + Product Demo)
We will build the **Landing Page** with the "Index" feature and **One Product Detail Page** demonstrating the "Re-Fit" switch.

